The paper deals with capacity achieving distributions for channels with memory and feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses time-varying channels with memory, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI). The use of recursive closed form expressions and investigation of asymptotic properties suggest that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the extension of the necessary and sufficient conditions to a variety of channels with memory, which suggests that it may also be relevant to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
